Curvelab-2.1.2-SLIM - CurveLab with SLIM's FFT Functions + Other.
(Read README.ORIG as well)
____________________________________________

Needed Programs:

1. FFTW 3.1.2+
	-> Used for fdct3d and fdct_wrapping_cpp, SLIM specific FFT functions.
	-> http://www.fftw.org

2. FFTW 2.1.5
	-> Needed for the other CurveLab Libraries, especially fdct3d_mpi.
	-> http://www.fftw.org

3. PetSC-2.3.2 or newer (Optional)
        -> Needed for fdct3d_mpi
        -> http://www-unix.mcs.anl.gov/petsc/petsc-as/

4. MATLAB
        -> for MATLAB components
____________________________________________

Installation:

1. Set FFTW3_DIR shell environment variable to the location of your FFTW (3.1.2)

2. Set FFTW_DIR shell environment variable to the location of your FFTW (2.1.5)

3. For non-MPI components:
	-> Run "make" in fdct3d/src AND fdct_wrapping_cpp/src folders (Only FFTW 3.1.2 needed).
	-> Run "make lib" in the main folder (Will produce errors if FFTW 2.1.5 folder (for default CurveLab functions) not set).

4. For MPI components (if needed):
        -> Set environment PETSC_DIR to home of PetSC installation
        -> Run "make mpi" in the mail folder
        -> Note printed PETSC_DIR and PETSC_ARCH (needed for MADAGASCAR compilation of SLIM MPI components))

5. MATLAB (if needed):
        -> Change MEX in makefile.opt and makefile.slim
        -> Run "make matlab" in the main folder

